@startuml

title NVI Integration

box "Healthcare Provider"
    actor User as "Clinician"
    participant emr as "EMR\n[FHIR]"
    participant kp as "Knooppunt"
end box

participant prs as "PRS\n(Pseudonymization\nService)"
participant nvi as "NVI\n(Nationale\nVerwijsIndex)"

== Flow 1: Register List (Making Data Available) ==

User -> emr : Register patient data\n(e.g. care episode started)

emr -> kp : [FHIR R4] POST /nvi/List\n(List with subject.identifier=BSN)\nX-Tenant-ID: {URA}

activate kp

note over kp, prs
  OPRF Protocol (RFC 9497) — Pseudonymization of BSN
end note

kp -> kp : Derive key using HKDF (RFC 5869)\nBlind BSN input (OPRF client blind)

kp -> prs : POST /evaluate\n(blinded BSN input, URA, audience="nvi", scope="nationale-verwijsindex")
activate prs
    prs -> prs : Evaluate blinded input\nwith PRS secret key
    prs --> kp : Evaluated blinded output (JWE)
deactivate prs

kp -> kp : Extract blind factor\nCompose transport token\n(system: BSN-pseudonym NamingSystem\nvalue: blindFactor + JWE)

kp -> kp : Replace List.subject.identifier\nwith pseudonymous transport token\nAdd custodian extension (URA)

kp -> nvi : [FHIR R4] POST /List\nAuthorization: Bearer {access_token}\n(List with pseudonymous subject identifier)
activate nvi
    nvi -> nvi : Deblind transport token → pseudonym\nStore {pseudonym, URA, careContext}
    nvi --> kp : 200 OK (List)
deactivate nvi

kp --> emr : 200 OK (List)
deactivate kp

== Flow 2: Query (Find Patients with Data Elsewhere) ==

User -> emr : Query NVI for patient\n(e.g. patient check-in)

note over emr, kp
  Required (at least one):
  - patient:identifier={BSNNamingSystem}|{BSN}  ← mapped to subject:identifier, BSN is tokenized
  - subject:identifier={BSNNamingSystem}|{BSN}  ← BSN is tokenized
  - source:identifier={system}|{deviceId}       ← passed through as-is (not tokenized)

  Optional:
  - code={system}|{code}   ← filter by data category (e.g. MedicationRequest)
  - _count={n}             ← max results per page
end note

emr -> kp : [FHIR R4] GET /nvi/List?patient:identifier={BSNNamingSystem}|{BSN}\n                        [&source:identifier={system}|{deviceId}]\n                        [&code={system}|{code}]\n                        [&_count={n}]\nX-Tenant-ID: {URA}

activate kp

note over kp, prs
  OPRF pseudonymization applied only to patient:identifier / subject:identifier (BSN)
  source:identifier and other params are forwarded unchanged
end note

kp -> kp : Blind BSN search token (OPRF client blind)

kp -> prs : POST /evaluate\n(blinded BSN input, URA, audience="nvi", scope="nationale-verwijsindex")
activate prs
    prs --> kp : Evaluated blinded output (JWE)
deactivate prs

kp -> kp : Compose pseudonymous search token\nMap patient:identifier → subject:identifier\nPass through source:identifier, code, _count unchanged

kp -> nvi : [FHIR R4] GET /List?subject:identifier={pseudonymous-token}\n                        [&source:identifier={system}|{deviceId}]\n                        [&code={system}|{code}]\n                        [&_count={n}]\nAuthorization: Bearer {access_token}
activate nvi
    nvi -> nvi : Deblind → pseudonym\nLookup matching List entries
    nvi --> kp : 200 OK (Bundle of List resources\nwith URA + careContext per match)
deactivate nvi

kp --> emr : 200 OK (Bundle)
deactivate kp

emr --> User : Show list of providers\nwho have data for this patient

@enduml
